{{wikipedia}}
==English==
=== Etymology ===
First attested 1710, from {{L.}}, literally ''from the former'', from [[priori]].

=== Adjective ===
'''a priori'''

#Known ahead of time.
#{{logic}} Based on hypothesis rather than experiment.
#:''a priori knowledge''

=== Adverb ===
'''a priori'''

#{{logic}} Derived by logic.

